Every day here has been 3 little history, or rather a turning over of pages of this tattered and shattered huge old stone book, in which the history of nearly half the world’s duration is written. A queer old collection of antiquities, now Pagan, now Christian, but> more frequently Pagan, Christian, Greek, Egyptian, Etruscan, Barbarian jumbled together—fine scope for the critical faculty in all its branches—a mine of learning half disinterred—art from the sublimest conception to the lowest balbos.
